review.reviewBody: Absolutely perfect temperature and the flavours were out of this world! Excellent Everything!
Country Style Perogies were so good ! I'll be trying other items soon
still very tasty, but i remember that the one pound of wings used to have a lot more wings!

The Cajun Chicken Pasta seems to have changed in the last 2 weeks because its gone from being a really nice flavourful cajun sauce and one of my favourites to being plain baked chiken breast and Alfredo sauce with no flavour and the consistency of rubber. Really not impressed.

i debated between 2 and 3 stars because the wings were good- but theyre quite pricy for what they are... and the country style pirogies were nasty. they werent cooked for my liking so they were mushy and lacked flavour. not to mention, the restaurant forgot the sour cream. the ranch they provided tasted like an off brand dip... overall just wasnt impressed with how expensive it was for such mediocre food.
